column20: My most salient characteristic is that I do things my way, daring to take risks. Once I have a goal that I would like to achieve, I am really determined to execute my plan and see through to make it to the top to finish it. When I became an equity analyst at a securities company, my senior colleagues urged me to choose safe sectors. However, I did not follow these advices because I would like to identify the next growth stocks even though those were very tiny at that time. The fact that if I had failed I would have been marked as incompetent scared me but I believed myself. After all, I predicted the surge in Chinese travelers to Korea and recommended relevant stocks, which generated a 500% yearly return and enabled me to be awarded 'Asia's Best Analyst' by Wall Street Journal.
